stateDiagram-v2

    [*] --> FullyFunctional

    FullyFunctional : Fully Functional<br/>--------<br/>All dependencies healthy<br/>SLO: 99.95% in window<br/>All features available<br/>Error budget: positive

    CoreFlowsOnly : Core Flows Only<br/>--------<br/>Non-essential dependencies degraded<br/>Critical paths still complete<br/>Notification, audit-log degraded<br/>Feature flags disable non-essentials

    ReadOnly : Read-Only Mode<br/>--------<br/>Primary write path unavailable<br/>Reads served from cache or replica<br/>Writes queued for replay<br/>Users see "saving disabled" banner

    SeverelyDegraded : Severely Degraded<br/>--------<br/>Multiple critical dependencies out<br/>Static fallback content served<br/>Cached responses with stale-warning<br/>Best-effort only

    Unavailable : Unavailable<br/>--------<br/>Critical-path dependencies all out<br/>RTO timer started<br/>Failover procedure invoked<br/>Status page reflects state

    FullyFunctional --> CoreFlowsOnly : Cache cluster failure<br/>OR notification service out
    FullyFunctional --> ReadOnly : Primary database write path failure
    FullyFunctional --> SeverelyDegraded : Multiple dependency failures<br/>(rare event)

    CoreFlowsOnly --> ReadOnly : Database write path also fails
    CoreFlowsOnly --> FullyFunctional : Degraded dependency recovers

    ReadOnly --> SeverelyDegraded : Read replicas also fail
    ReadOnly --> FullyFunctional : Primary write path restored<br/>queued writes replayed

    SeverelyDegraded --> Unavailable : Last-resort fallback exhausted
    SeverelyDegraded --> ReadOnly : Reads recover, writes still down
    SeverelyDegraded --> FullyFunctional : Full recovery (RTO met)

    Unavailable --> SeverelyDegraded : Failover completes,<br/>limited service restored
    Unavailable --> FullyFunctional : Full failover successful<br/>(within RTO target)

    note right of CoreFlowsOnly
      Feature flags activate
      bulkheads isolate
      non-essential deps
    end note

    note right of ReadOnly
      RPO clock running:
      time-of-failure recorded
      writes preserved in queue
    end note
